The paper deals with interference management in uplink cellular networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of message passing and routing also suggests a possible connection to distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper's focus on network topology and combinatorial optimization may also place it in the subfield of social and information networks (cs.SI).
